    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - FUEL SYSTEM - Fuel Transfer
        Pump
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>Fuel Transfer Pump</title>
        <svcproc graphiccount="1">
            <title>Removal</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The fuel supply tube that is shown is for engine models with non-split shot fuel systems (S/N
                        460194 and earlier).
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f1201216" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg3/eg3287.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
                <caption>Removing the Fuel Transfer Pump</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Transfer Pump</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply Tube to Cylinder Head Galleries</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Tube Bolt</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Supply Tube Nuts (2)</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel supply tube bolt at the base of the fuel transfer pump.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen the nuts of the fuel supply tubes at the cylinder heads. Remove the fuel supply
                    tube from the engine.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two mounting bolts that secure the fuel transfer pump to the base of the
                    crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Rotate the engine by hand until the pump is pushed up approximately 1/2 inch. This
                    places the cam lobe at the top. In this position, if the tappet falls out of the pump during
                    removal, it will not enter the crankcase.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the fuel transfer pump.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If required, retrieve the tappet from the fuel transfer pump bore located in the
                    crankcase. Insert the tappet into the base of the pump.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
